// Gate-1b: integer modulo-by-zero. srem shares sdiv's zero-divisor trap
// (STATUS_INTEGER_DIVIDE_BY_ZERO 0xC0000094) — the interpreter raises a clean
// DivByZero error (exit 1). The JIT now emits the same divisor==0 guard as Div
// (Mod needs only this — srem already handles INT_MIN%-1), branching to the
// cx_trap clean exit (126). Both backends reject non-zero → convergent
// expected-fail PASS. Width-general — see _t8/_t64 siblings.
a: t32 = 5
b: t32 = 0
print(a % b)
